parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to sudden loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The tire tread comes off suddenly
and noise. The tire may remain inflated

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Contamination with Metal Particles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of fine metal particles in the engine oil can lead to premature engine wear, damage to moving parts, and potentially cause engine failure, resulting in costly repairs or even engine replacement.
symptoms: Sharp rapping or tapping sound upon initial engine startup
visible metal particles in the oil drain pan
